'''Florian Wiegele''' (born 21 March 2001) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň]] and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].

==Early life==
Wiegele was born on 21 March 2001 in [[Austria]] and is a native of [[Graz]], Austria. Growing up, he regarded [[Germany national football team|Germany]] international [[Manuel Neuer]] as his football idol and has been nicknamed "Langer".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kleinezeitung.at/sport/fussball/oesterreich/bundesliga/sksturm/19446647/florian-wiegele-und-kjell-scherpen-sorgen-fuer-das-groesste-grazer|title=Florian Wiegele und Kjell Scherpen sorgen für das größte Grazer Derby aller Zeiten|trans-title=Florian Wiegele and Kjell Scherpen ensure the greatest Graz derby of all time|language=de|publisher=[[Kleine Zeitung]]|date=8 March 2025|access-date=17 May 2025}}</ref>

==Career==
Wiegele started his career with the [[reserve team]] of Austrian side [[SK Sturm Graz]] in 2017. Two years later, he signed for Austrian side SV Lebring. In 2022, he signed for Austrian side FC Gleisdorf 09, where he made twenty-four league appearances and scored zero goals. During the summer of 2023, he signed for Austrian side [[DSV Leoben]], where he made twelve league appearances and scored zero goals and suffered relegation from the [[2. Liga (Austria)|second tier]] to the [[Austrian Regionalliga|third tier]] while playing for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-chance-liga-rocnik-2024-25/449773/dvanactka-novacku-plzne-klenot-do-zakladu-obr-v-brane-i-strelci.html|title=Dvanáctka nováčků Plzně: klenot do základu, obr v bráně i střelci|trans-title=Plzeň's twelve newcomers: a gem in the foundation, a giant in goal and scorers|language=cs|publisher=[[Blesk]]|date=16 July 2024|access-date=17 May 2025}}</ref>

Ahead of the [[2024–25 Czech First League|2024–25 season]], he signed for Czech side [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]]. Six months later, he was sent on loan to Austrian side [[Grazer AK]]. German magazine [[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] wrote in 2025 that he "immediately established himself as the number one goalie for GAK, pushing promotion hero [[Jakob Meierhofer]] to the bench" while playing for the club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kicker.de/der-sonntag-mit-rugby-schuhen-und-papa-soehnen-1091015/artikel|title=Der Sonntag mit Rugby-Schuhen und Papa-Söhne|trans-title=Sunday with rugby shoes and daddy's sons|language=de|publisher=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]]|date=16 February 2025|access-date=17 May 2025}}</ref>
He had great half of the season in Grazer and he came back to Viktoria Plzeň where he is fighting for the number one.

Wiegele was named in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup squads#Austria|Austria squad for the 2026 Men's World Cup]]<ref>{{Cite web |title=Alaba, Arnautovic feature as Austria name World Cup squad |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/austria-ralf-rangnick-world-cup-squad |access-date=2026-06-03 |website=www.fifa.com}}</ref> and at 2.05m, became the tallest player to ever make a World Cup squad.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/numbers-squads-stats |access-date=2026-06-03 |website=www.fifa.com|title=The squads in stats}}</ref>

